{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844717504,"sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","part":{"id":"prt_d7897ef98001R5CuuvuEHQZJwz","messageID":"msg_d7897e312001m6Sjxv26Vqbvae","sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c240b2236ae4422780ebab58","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`, providing comprehensive control over sandbox termination, graceful shutdown, TTL/expiration handling, and resource cleanup. This extends the sandbox creation capabilities from AR-005 with complete lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: AR-005 provides sandbox creation capabilities, but production environments require robust deletion handling to:\n12: - Gracefully terminate active sandboxes without disrupting in-flight requests\n13: - Enforce TTL and idle timeout policies for resource optimization\n14: - Clean up associated Kubernetes resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n15: - Provide audit trails and lifecycle events for operational visibility\n16: \n17: ### Goal\n18: \n19: Provide a production-ready sandbox deletion and lifecycle management system that:\n20: - Supports graceful termination with connection draining\n21: - Enforces TTL, idle timeout, and max lifetime policies\n22: - Handles batch deletion and label-based filtering\n23: - Emits lifecycle events and webhooks for external integrations\n24: - Properly cleans up all associated Kubernetes resources\n25: \n26: ### Value\n27: - Prevents resource leaks through automated cleanup\n28: - Enables policy-driven sandbox lifecycle management\n29: - Provides operational auditability for compliance\n30: - Supports zero-downtime deployments through graceful shutdown\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Scope\n35: \n36: ### In-Scope\n37: \n38: | Deliverable | Description |\n39: |-------------|-------------|\n40: | Deletion Handlers | HTTP handlers for DELETE by SessionID/name, force delete |\n41: | Graceful Shutdown | Connection draining, pre-delete hooks, SIGTERM handling |\n42: | TTL/Expiration | TTL enforcement, idle timeout, max lifetime garbage collection |\n43: | Batch Operations | Delete all in namespace, label selector deletion, stale cleanup |\n44: | Lifecycle Events | K8s events, webhooks, audit logging |\n45: | Resource Cleanup | Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs, orphaned resources |\n46: \n47: ### API Endpoints\n48: \n49: #### Sandbox Deletion\n50: | Method | Path | Description |\n51: |--------|------|-------------|\n52: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}` | Delete sandbox by SessionID |\n53: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/name/{name}` | Delete sandbox by name |\n54: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | Delete all in namespace |\n55: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n56: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n57: \n58: #### Query Parameters\n59: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n60: |-----------|------|-------------|\n61: | gracePeriodSeconds | int | Seconds to wait before force termination |\n62: | force | bool | Force deletion bypassing finalizers |\n63: | deleteAll | bool | Delete all sandboxes in namespace |\n64: | labelSelector | string | Label selector for filtered deletion |\n65: \n66: ### Code Structure\n67: \n68: ```\n69: pkg/workloadmanager/\n70: ├── server.go                    # HTTP server (existing)\n71: ├── service.go                   # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n72: ├── types.go                     # API types (existing)\n73: ├── client.go                    # Kubernetes client (existing)\n74: ├── handlers.go                  # Existing handlers + delete handlers\n75: ├── delete_options.go            # DeleteOptions struct\n76: ├── graceful_shutdown.go         # Graceful termination logic\n77: ├── garbage_collector.go        # TTL/idle/maxLifetime enforcement\n78: ├── expiration.go                # isExpired() helpers\n79: ├── batch_delete.go              # Batch deletion operations\n80: ├── lifecycle_events.go          # Event emission, webhooks, audit\n81: ├── resource_cleanup.go          # Service/ConfigMap/PVC cleanup\n82: ├── retry.go                     # Retry logic for failed deletions\n83: └── sandbox/\n84:     └── (from AR-005)\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### Out-of-Scope\n88: - Sandbox scaling (AR-005)\n89: - Sandbox monitoring/alerting (separate observability module)\n90: - Multi-cluster deletion (future enhancement)\n91: - Sandbox migration between namespaces (future enhancement)\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Impact Analysis\n96: \n97: ### Dependencies\n98: \n99: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n100: |------------|--------|---------|\n101: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client |\n102: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager | local | Existing WorkloadManager |\n103: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | local | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter types |\n104: | k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime | ^1.34 | Object serialization |\n105: | k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1 | ^1.34 | metav1 types |\n106: | k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes | ^1.34 | Kubernetes client |\n107: \n108: ### Upstream Dependencies\n109: \n110: - **AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)** — Provides sandbox creation and management foundation\n111: - **AR-004 WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework** — Provides HTTP server infrastructure\n112: \n113: ### Downstream Consumers\n114: \n115: 1. **Garbage Collection Jobs** — Automated cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes\n116: 2. **CI/CD Pipelines** — Ephemeral sandbox cleanup after tests\n117: 3. **Operator Controllers** — Kubernetes-native lifecycle management\n118: 4. **Monitoring Systems** — Lifecycle event consumption\n119: \n120: ### Risks\n121: \n122: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n123: |------|----------|------------|\n124: | Resource orphaning | High | Finalizers, ownerReferences, cleanup verification |\n125: | Stuck terminating Pods | Medium | Force deletion with gracePeriodSeconds=0 |\n126: | Cascading failures | Medium | Retry with exponential backoff, error propagation |\n127: | Data loss | High | ReclaimPolicy handling for PVCs, confirmation for force delete |\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## Alternatives Considered\n132: \n133: ### Option 1: Direct Kubernetes Deletion (Selected)\n134: \n135: **Approach**: Implement deletion handlers that directly interact with Kubernetes API, using ownerReferences and finalizers for cleanup.\n136: \n137: **Pros**:\n138: - Native Kubernetes patterns\n139: - Leverages existing client-go infrastructure\n140: - Automatic cleanup through garbage collection\n141: - Well-understood failure modes\n142: \n143: **Cons**:\n144: - Requires understanding of K8s delete semantics\n145: - Limited control over graceful termination timing\n146: \n147: **Decision**: Selected — provides the best integration with Kubernetes ecosystem.\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ### Option 2: Sidecar-based Lifecycle Manager\n152: \n153: **Approach**: Deploy a sidecar container in each sandbox that handles lifecycle events.\n154: \n155: **Pros**:\n156: - Granular control over individual sandbox lifecycle\n157: - Isolation from workload manager\n158: \n159: **Cons**:\n160: - Additional resource overhead per sandbox\n161: - Complex sidecar communication\n162: - Overhead for current requirements\n163: \n164: **Decision**: Rejected — adds unnecessary complexity.\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Option 3: External Deletion Service\n169: \n170: **Approach**: Implement sandbox deletion as a separate microservice with its own API.\n171: \n172: **Pros**:\n173: - Independent scaling\n174: - Complete isolation\n175: \n176: **Cons**:\n177: - Additional infrastructure\n178: - Network latency\n179: - Duplicate logic with existing service\n180: \n181: **Decision**: Rejected — unnecessary operational complexity.\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ### Option 4: Operator Pattern with Custom CRD\n186: \n187: **Approach**: Implement a full Kubernetes operator for sandbox lifecycle.\n188: \n189: **Pros**:\n190: - Native reconciliation\n191: - Automatic retry and healing\n192: \n193: **Cons**:\n194: - Higher implementation complexity\n195: - Separate deployment\n196: - Overkill for current scale\n197: \n198: **Decision**: Rejected — can be considered as future enhancement when more advanced reconciliation is needed.\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## Implementation Plan\n203: \n204: ### Phase 1: Deletion Handlers\n205: - [ ] Add handleSandboxDelete() for DELETE by SessionID\n206: - [ ] Add handleSandboxDeleteByName() for DELETE by name\n207: - [ ] Register DELETE routes in server.go\n208: - [ ] Implement DeleteOptions struct\n209: \n210: ### Phase 2: Graceful Shutdown\n211: - [ ] Implement gracefulDeleter with drainConnections()\n212: - [ ] Implement waitForConnections() with timeout\n213: - [ ] Implement executePreDeleteHook()\n214: - [ ] Implement sendSIGTERM() to containers\n215: \n216: ### Phase 3: TTL and Expiration\n217: - [ ] Update garbage_collector.go with TTL check\n218: - [ ] Add idle timeout detection\n219: - [ ] Add max lifetime enforcement\n220: - [ ] Implement isExpired() helper\n221: \n222: ### Phase 4: Batch Operations\n223: - [ ] Implement handleDeleteAllSandboxes()\n224: - [ ] Implement handleDeleteByLabelSelector()\n225: - [ ] Implement deleteStaleSandboxes()\n226: \n227: ### Phase 5: Lifecycle Events\n228: - [ ] Implement emitDeletionEvent() using event recorder\n229: - [ ] Implement sendDeletionWebhook() with retry\n230: - [ ] Implement logDeletionAudit()\n231: \n232: ### Phase 6: Resource Cleanup\n233: - [ ] Implement cleanupServices()\n234: - [ ] Implement cleanupConfigMaps()\n235: - [ ] Implement cleanupPVCs() with ReclaimPolicy\n236: - [ ] Implement cleanupOrphanedResources()\n237: \n238: ### Phase 7: Error Handling\n239: - [ ] Add ErrSandboxNotFound, ErrDeletionFailed error types\n240: - [ ] Map errors to HTTP status codes\n241: - [ ] Implement retryDeletion() with backoff\n242: \n243: ### Phase 8: Testing\n244: - [ ] Unit tests for deletion handlers\n245: - [ ] Graceful shutdown tests\n246: - [ ] TTL/idle timeout tests\n247: - [ ] Batch deletion tests\n248: - [ ] Integration tests\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## Acceptance Criteria\n253: \n254: - [ ] DELETE by SessionID returns 200 OK and cleans up resources\n255: - [ ] DELETE by name returns 200 OK and cleans up resources\n256: - [ ] Force deletion bypasses finalizers when gracePeriodSeconds=0\n257: - [ ] DELETE non-existent sandbox returns 404 Not Found\n258: - [ ] Graceful termination waits for connections before force kill\n259: - [ ] Pre-delete hooks execute before deletion proceeds\n260: - [ ] TTL enforcement automatically deletes expired sandboxes\n261: - [ ] Idle timeout terminates inactive sandboxes\n262: - [ ] Batch deletion with label selectors works correctly\n263: - [ ] Associated Services/ConfigMaps are cleaned up\n264: - [ ] PVC cleanup respects ReclaimPolicy\n265: - [ ] Lifecycle events are emitted to Kubernetes\n266: - [ ] Webhooks are sent with retry on failure\n267: - [ ] Audit logs capture deletion details\n268: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >40% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 268 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`, providing comprehensive control over sandbox termination, graceful shutdown, TTL/expiration handling, and resource cleanup. This extends the sandbox creation capabilities from AR-005 with complete lifecycle management.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAR-005 provides sandbox creation capabilities, but production environments require robust deletion handling to:\n- Gracefully terminate active sandboxes without disrupting in-flight requests\n- Enforce TTL and idle timeout policies for resource optimization\n- Clean up associated Kubernetes resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n- Provide audit trails and lifecycle events for operational visibility\n\n### Goal\n\nProvide a production-ready sandbox deletion and lifecycle management system that:\n- Supports graceful termination with connection draining","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775844717483,"end":1775844717502}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844717509,"sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","part":{"id":"prt_d7897f1a4001nODEIXWEvk3M0S","messageID":"msg_d7897e312001m6Sjxv26Vqbvae","sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_00450e2d9afd41baa699369f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"errors\"\n5: \t\"time\"\n6: \n7: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n8: )\n9: \n10: var (\n11: \tErrSandboxNotFound    = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n12: \tErrDeletionFailed     = errors.New(\"deletion failed\")\n13: \tErrStaleFinalizer     = errors.New(\"stale finalizer\")\n14: \tErrOrphanedResource   = errors.New(\"orphaned resource\")\n15: \tErrResourceNotFound   = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n16: \tErrResourceNotDeleted = errors.New(\"resource not deleted\")\n17: )\n18: \n19: type DeleteOptions struct {\n20: \tGracePeriodSeconds *int64 `form:\"gracePeriodSeconds,omitempty\" json:\"gracePeriodSeconds,omitempty\"`\n21: \tForce              bool   `form:\"force\" json:\"force,omitempty\"`\n22: \tLabelSelector      string `form:\"labelSelector\" json:\"labelSelector,omitempty\"`\n23: \tPreconditions      *Preconditions\n24: }\n25: \n26: type Preconditions struct {\n27: \tUID             string `json:\"uid,omitempty\"`\n28: \tResourceVersion string `json:\"resourceVersion,omitempty\"`\n29: }\n30: \n31: type WebhookConfig struct {\n32: \tURL        string `json:\"url\"`\n33: \tTimeout    int    `json:\"timeout\"`\n34: \tRetryCount int    `json:\"retryCount\"`\n35: }\n36: \n37: type AuditLogEntry struct {\n38: \tSandboxID        string      `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n39: \tNamespace        string      `json:\"namespace\"`\n40: \tReason           string      `json:\"reason\"`\n41: \tInitiator        string      `json:\"initiator\"`\n42: \tDuration         int64       `json:\"duration\"`\n43: \tResourcesCleaned []string    `json:\"resourcesCleaned\"`\n44: \tTimestamp        metav1.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n45: }\n46: \n47: type DeletionEvent struct {\n48: \tType           string      `json:\"type\"`\n49: \tReason         string      `json:\"reason\"`\n50: \tMessage        string      `json:\"message\"`\n51: \tInvolvedObject string      `json:\"involvedObject\"`\n52: \tTimestamp      metav1.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n53: }\n54: \n55: type Sandbox struct {\n56: \tName           string            `json:\"name\"`\n57: \tNamespace      string            `json:\"namespace\"`\n58: \tSessionID      string            `json:\"sessionId\"`\n59: \tState          SandboxState      `json:\"state\"`\n60: \tCreatedAt      time.Time         `json:\"createdAt\"`\n61: \tExpiresAt      *time.Time        `json:\"expiresAt,omitempty\"`\n62: \tLastActivityAt *time.Time        `json:\"lastActivityAt,omitempty\"`\n63: \tLabels         map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n64: \tAnnotations    map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n65: }\n66: \n67: type SandboxState string\n68: \n69: const (\n70: \tSandboxStateUnknown  SandboxState = \"Unknown\"\n71: \tSandboxStatePending  SandboxState = \"Pending\"\n72: \tSandboxStateRunning  SandboxState = \"Running\"\n73: \tSandboxStateFailed   SandboxState = \"Failed\"\n74: \tSandboxStateDeleting SandboxState = \"Deleting\"\n75: )\n76: \n77: type SandboxList struct {\n78: \tItems []Sandbox `json:\"items\"`\n79: }\n80: \n81: type ListOptions struct {\n82: \tLabelSelector string `form:\"labelSelector\"`\n83: \tFieldSelector string `form:\"fieldSelector\"`\n84: \tLimit         int64  `form:\"limit\"`\n85: \tContinue      string `form:\"continue\"`\n86: }\n87: \n88: type DeleteResponse struct {\n89: \tName             string      `json:\"name\"`\n90: \tNamespace        string      `json:\"namespace\"`\n91: \tDeletedAt        metav1.Time `json:\"deletedAt\"`\n92: \tResourcesCleaned []string    `json:\"resourcesCleaned\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: type BatchDeleteResponse struct {\n96: \tDeletedCount int      `json:\"deletedCount\"`\n97: \tFailedCount  int      `json:\"failedCount\"`\n98: \tErrors       []string `json:\"errors,omitempty\"`\n99: }\n100: \n101: type APIResponse struct {\n102: \tKind       string      `json:\"kind\"`\n103: \tAPIVersion string      `json:\"apiVersion\"`\n104: \tStatus     string      `json:\"status\"`\n105: \tData       interface{} `json:\"data,omitempty\"`\n106: \tMetadata   *ListMeta   `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n107: }\n108: \n109: type ListMeta struct {\n110: \tContinue           string `json:\"continue,omitempty\"`\n111: \tRemainingItemCount *int64 `json:\"remainingItemCount,omitempty\"`\n112: \tResourceVersion    string `json:\"resourceVersion,omitempty\"`\n113: }\n114: \n115: type APIError struct {\n116: \tKind       string           `json:\"kind\"`\n117: \tAPIVersion string           `json:\"apiVersion\"`\n118: \tStatus     string           `json:\"status\"`\n119: \tMessage    string           `json:\"message\"`\n120: \tReason     string           `json:\"reason\"`\n121: \tCode       int              `json:\"code\"`\n122: \tDetails    *APIErrorDetails `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n123: }\n124: \n125: type APIErrorDetails struct {\n126: \tName   string          `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n127: \tGroup  string          `json:\"group,omitempty\"`\n128: \tKind   string          `json:\"kind,omitempty\"`\n129: \tUID    string          `json:\"uid,omitempty\"`\n130: \tCauses []APIErrorCause `json:\"causes,omitempty\"`\n131: }\n132: \n133: type APIErrorCause struct {\n134: \tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n135: \tField   string `json:\"field\"`\n136: }\n137: \n138: type PaginationRequest struct {\n139: \tLimit    int64  `form:\"limit\"`\n140: \tContinue string `form:\"continue\"`\n141: }\n142: \n143: type PaginationResponse struct {\n144: \tItems              interface{} `json:\"items\"`\n145: \tListMeta           *ListMeta   `json:\"metadata\"`\n146: \tRemainingItemCount *int64      `json:\"remainingItemCount,omitempty\"`\n147: }\n148: \n149: type AgentRuntimeListResponse struct {\n150: \tKind       string             `json:\"kind\"`\n151: \tAPIVersion string             `json:\"apiVersion\"`\n152: \tItems      []AgentRuntimeItem `json:\"items\"`\n153: \t*ListMeta\n154: }\n155: \n156: type AgentRuntimeItem struct {\n157: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n158: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n159: \tSpec              interface{} `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n160: \tStatus            interface{} `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n161: }\n162: \n163: type CodeInterpreterListResponse struct {\n164: \tKind       string                `json:\"kind\"`\n165: \tAPIVersion string                `json:\"apiVersion\"`\n166: \tItems      []CodeInterpreterItem `json:\"items\"`\n167: \t*ListMeta\n168: }\n169: \n170: type CodeInterpreterItem struct {\n171: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n172: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n173: \tSpec              interface{} `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n174: \tStatus            interface{} `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n175: }\n176: \n177: type CreateAgentRuntimeRequest struct {\n178: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n179: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n180: \tSpec              interface{} `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n181: }\n182: \n183: type CreateCodeInterpreterRequest struct {\n184: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n185: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n186: \tSpec              interface{} `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n187: }\n188: \n189: type UpdateAgentRuntimeRequest struct {\n190: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n191: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n192: \tSpec              interface{} `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n193: }\n194: \n195: type UpdateCodeInterpreterRequest struct {\n196: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n197: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n198: \tSpec              interface{} `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n199: }\n200: \n201: type WatchEvent struct {\n202: \tType   string      `json:\"type\"`\n203: \tObject interface{} `json:\"object\"`\n204: }\n205: \n206: func NewAPIResponse(data interface{}, metadata *ListMeta) *APIResponse {\n207: \treturn &APIResponse{\n208: \t\tKind:       \"Status\",\n209: \t\tAPIVersion: \"v1\",\n210: \t\tStatus:     \"Success\",\n211: \t\tData:       data,\n212: \t\tMetadata:   metadata,\n213: \t}\n214: }\n215: \n216: func NewAPIError(message, reason string, code int) *APIError {\n217: \treturn &APIError{\n218: \t\tKind:       \"Status\",\n219: \t\tAPIVersion: \"v1\",\n220: \t\tStatus:     \"Failure\",\n221: \t\tMessage:    message,\n222: \t\tReason:     reason,\n223: \t\tCode:       code,\n224: \t}\n225: }\n\n(End of file - total 225 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tErrSandboxNotFound    = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n\tErrDeletionFailed     = errors.New(\"deletion failed\")\n\tErrStaleFinalizer     = errors.New(\"stale finalizer\")\n\tErrOrphanedResource   = errors.New(\"orphaned resource\")\n\tErrResourceNotFound   = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n\tErrResourceNotDeleted = errors.New(\"resource not deleted\")\n)\n\ntype DeleteOptions struct {\n\tGracePeriodSeconds *int64 `form:\"gracePeriodSeconds,omitempty\" json:\"gracePeriodSeconds,omitempty\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go","time":{"start":1775844717486,"end":1775844717507}}}}
