{"type":"text","timestamp":1775844742595,"sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","part":{"id":"prt_d78985479001i04GNnqHBER5K8","messageID":"msg_d78984318001OOJNGuwyx0SAbq","sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context. Let me write the proposal for AR-007.","time":{"start":1775844742593,"end":1775844742593}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844773620,"sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","part":{"id":"prt_d789855c30015isKlvJ3rbDmSI","messageID":"msg_d78984318001OOJNGuwyx0SAbq","sessionID":"ses_287683e44ffeZQiBMgUyL7O3Se","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ded78401e9d5496fbf5580f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement a Kubernetes Reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` to provide native, declarative lifecycle management for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. This transforms the current imperative HTTP API into a Kubernetes-native controller pattern that automatically reconciles desired state with actual cluster state.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAR-004 and AR-005/AR-006 provide HTTP API endpoints for creating and managing sandboxes through imperative requests. However, production environments require:\n\n- **Declarative resource management**: Users define desired state via CRDs, and the controller ensures the cluster matches\n- **Automatic reconciliation**: Self-healing when pods crash, configuration drifts, or external changes occur\n- **Status synchronization**: Real-time status updates reflecting actual resource state\n- **Event-driven updates**: React to cluster events without polling\n- **Integration with K8s ecosystem**: Works with kubectl, Helm, ArgoCD, and other native tools\n\n### Goal\n\nProvide a production-ready Kubernetes controller that:\n- Watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs and reconciles them to desired state\n- Automatically creates/updates/deletes underlying Pods, Services, ConfigMaps, and PVCs\n- Emits status conditions reflecting actual resource state\n- Handles requeues and exponential backoff for transient failures\n- Supports finalizers for graceful deletion\n\n### Value\n- Enables GitOps workflows for sandbox management\n- Self-healing and idempotent operations\n- Unified Kubernetes-native management interface\n- Reduced operational complexity through automation\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| Controller Implementation | core reconciler logic for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n| Informer Integration | Using client-go informers for event-driven reconciliation |\n| Resource Provisioning | Pod, Service, ConfigMap, PVC creation from CR specs |\n| Status Reconciliation | Update CR status with current state and conditions |\n| Requeue Logic | Exponential backoff for failed reconciliations |\n| Finalizer Management | Graceful deletion with resource cleanup |\n| Unit Tests | Controller logic coverage >60% |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── server.go                           # HTTP server (existing)\n├── service.go                          # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n├── types.go                            # API types (existing)\n├── client.go                           # Kubernetes client (existing)\n├── controller/\n│   ├── controller.go                   # Main controller setup\n│   ├── reconciler.go                   # Reconciler implementation\n│   ├── agentruntime_reconciler.go    # AgentRuntime-specific logic\n│   ├── codeinterpreter_reconciler.go # CodeInterpreter-specific logic\n│   ├── builder.go                     # Builder pattern for controller\n│   ├── finalizers.go                  # Finalizer management\n│   └── status.go                      # Status condition updates\n├── reconciler/\n│   ├── pod.go                         # Pod creation/management\n│   ├── service.go                    # Service creation/management\n│   ├── configmap.go                  # ConfigMap creation/management\n│   └── pvc.go                        # PVC creation/management\n└── events/\n    ├── recorder.go                    # Event recording\n    └── events.go                      # Event types\n```\n\n### API Changes\n\nThe controller operates on existing CRDs without new API endpoints. However, it enhances the behavior of existing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources:\n\n#### Status Conditions\n\nThe controller populates these status conditions:\n\n| Condition | Status | Reason | Description |\n|-----------|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Initialized | True/False | Initialized | CRD schema validated |\n| PodCreated | True/False | PodCreated | Pod resource created |\n| Ready | True/False | Ready | All resources ready |\n| Failed | True/False | Reason | Reconciliation failed |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Webhook admission controllers (future enhancement)\n- Multi-cluster reconciliation (future enhancement)\n- Custom metrics server (separate observability module)\n- Horizontal pod autoscaling (separate feature)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager | local | Existing WorkloadManager |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | local | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter types |\n| k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller | ^0.20 | Controller base |\n| k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client | ^0.20 | Client interface |\n| k8s.io/client-go/informers | ^0.34 | Cached watch support |\n| k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache | ^0.34 | Informer handlers |\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n- **AR-004 WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework** — Provides HTTP server infrastructure\n- **AR-005/AR-006 Sandbox Creation/Deletion** — Controller manages resources created by these\n- **client-go library** — Generated typed clients for runtime/v1alpha1\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Kubernetes Controller Manager** — Runs the controller as part of control plane\n2. **kubectl users** — See status of AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n3. **GitOps tools** — ArgoCD, Flux for declarative sandbox management\n4. **Monitoring systems** — Consume status conditions for alerting\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Resource conflicts | High | OwnerReferences for cascading deletion |\n| Memory leaks | Medium | Proper informer teardown, client caching |\n| Reconcile loops | Medium | Requeue limits, predicate filtering |\n| Status race conditions | Medium | Optimistic locking via resourceVersion |\n| Partial failure | Medium | Transactional updates, status last update |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Controller-runtime Based Controller (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Use `controller-runtime` library to implement a Kubernetes controller.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Well-established patterns for K8s controllers\n- Built-in informer caching and leader election\n- Integrates with kubebuilder for deployment\n- Familiar to Kubernetes developers\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional dependency on controller-runtime\n- Learning curve for existing team\n\n**Decision**: Selected — provides the most robust and production-tested approach.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Custom Controller with client-go\n\n**Approach**: Build a custom controller using raw client-go informers without controller-runtime.\n\n**Pros**:\n- No additional dependencies\n- Fine-grained control over reconciliation logic\n\n**Cons**:\n- Reinventing caching, leader election, metrics\n- Higher maintenance burden\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — unnecessary complexity for this use case.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Operator SDK\n\n**Approach**: Use Operator SDK to scaffold and build the controller.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Complete scaffolding and boilerplate\n- Built-in CLI for deployment\n- Integration with OLM\n\n**Cons**:\n- Heavyweight for this use case\n- Additional abstraction layer\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — controller-runtime provides sufficient abstraction without full Operator SDK overhead.\n\n---\n\n### Option 4: External Controller Service\n\n**Approach**: Implement controller as a separate microservice not embedded in workloadmanager.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Independent scaling and deployment\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional infrastructure\n- Network overhead for client-go communication\n- Duplicated code with existing workloadmanager\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — tightly coupling with workloadmanager provides better resource sharing and simpler deployment.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Controller Foundation\n- [ ] Add controller-runtime dependency to go.mod\n- [ ] Create controller.go with controller manager setup\n- [ ] Implement Builder pattern for controller registration\n- [ ] Add predicate filters for namespace/type selection\n\n### Phase 2: AgentRuntime Reconciler\n- [ ] Implement AgentRuntimeReconciler struct\n- [ ] Reconcile() method with resource lookup and diff\n- [ ] Pod creation from AgentRuntimeSpec\n- [ ] Service creation for TargetPorts\n- [ ] Status condition updates\n\n### Phase 3: CodeInterpreter Reconciler\n- [ ] Implement CodeInterpreterReconciler struct\n- [ ] Container template processing\n- [ ] Warm pool management\n- [ ] Auth mode handling\n\n### Phase 4: Resource Management\n- [ ] Implement Pod/ReplicaSet management\n- [ ] Implement Service management\n- [ ] Implement ConfigMap management\n- [ ] Implement PVC management for storage\n\n### Phase 5: Advanced Features\n- [ ] Add finalizers for graceful deletion\n- [ ] Implement exponential backoff requeue\n- [ ] Add event recording\n- [ ] Implement ownerReference for cascading deletion\n\n### Phase 6: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for reconciler logic\n- [ ] Mock tests for K8s client interactions\n- [ ] Integration tests with mock API server\n- [ ] Chaos testing for reconcile loops\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Controller starts and watches AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n- [ ] Creating AgentRuntime triggers Pod/Service creation\n- [ ] Updating AgentRuntime spec triggers resource update\n- [ ] Deleting AgentRuntime triggers resource cleanup with finalizer\n- [ ] Status conditions accurately reflect resource state\n- [ ] Reconcile fails gracefully with proper error handling\n- [ ] Controller handles namespace-scoped resources correctly\n- [ ] Events are recorded for key lifecycle operations\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >60% coverage\n- [ ] Controller integrates with existing workloadmanager deployment","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go\">\nERROR [94:16] undefined: metav1\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go\">\nERROR [15:2] \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch\" imported and not used\nERROR [66:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [81:9] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [95:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [109:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [132:14] cannot us